+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019kfhkkhA5Su25cC77JjWVQ","type":"tool_result","content":"# Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n\nAdd per-queue limits on how many tasks can be processed at the same time.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Each queue can have a maximum concurrency setting that limits how many tasks can be in a processing state simultaneously.\n- If the concurrency limit is reached, retrieving a task returns `null` even if pending tasks are available.\n- Completing or failing a task frees up a concurrency slot.\n- By default, queues have no concurrency limit (unlimited).\n- There should be a way to set and query the concurrency limit and current active count for a queue.\n- Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering -- the highest-priority available task is still chosen, subject to the concurrency limit.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011uLaT5pe9oCp43U7MibrtW","session_id":"139f6207-0d76-4c67-a3f1-139634183078","uuid":"71c71f43-03b1-4ae5-a892-ebd08ef898b8"}
